<font face="Arial" size="2">Thank you very much, <lj user="elanna9">, for the beautiful yellow rose! You really brightened my day!

A very happy Valentine to you and your family!

Lots of love,
Lili</font>

Just a temporary pop out of the silence to say:

HAPPY BIRTHDAY

Have the best one ever and may everything that you hope for come true!

Love from the silhouette in the shadows.

Lili

Happy birthday

 

I hope you'll have a great day!

I came back yesterday from what was a wonderful vacation. Not exactly relaxing, rock-climbing for more than a month isn't supposed to be, but very refreshing.

And today I'm back at work (sigh.)

During my time off LJ I've done some thinking about this whole thing. What I really like to do here is to read and write fics. Due to very limited time from now on that's ALL I'm going to do, otherwise I'm never going to be able to finish my WIPS.Or to be honest, write anything at all, which I really would like to do.

About reading I have missed a lot and I'm going to spend the following days trying to catch up with it as much as I can and leave some belated feedback.

I'm, going to repost my stories later, when I've written so much that I can post on a regular basis.

Love to everyone that bother to read this.

Lili

So it's finally here, my vacation. I'm really looking forward to it after this more than hectic year.

I'm going to be offline for at least a month, will most likely be back sometime in August.

Take care everybody!

A very happy birthday to the lovely

 

I hope you'll have a wonderful day sweetie!

I'm so glad to have gotten to know you here on LJ. You're such a warm and caring person that always seem to have a kind word for everyone.

Love to you!

And happy 4th July to all Americans!

Look, what the absolutely awesome
made for me, I'm absolutely stunned, I don't have words enough to thank you!



A perfect choice for me.
I LOVE YOU!

Some parts of this are actually frightenly accurate....

 

Take the quiz: "What does your birth month reveal about you?"

November
Has lots of extraordinary ideas. Difficult to fathom. Thinkforward. Unique. brilliant. Sharp thinking. Fine, strong clairvoyance. make good doctors. Dynamic. Secretive. Inquisitive. Know how to dig secrets. Always thinking. Less talkative. amiable. Brave. generous. Patient. Stubborn. hardhearted. Determined. Never quit. Hardly become angry unless provoked. Love to be alone. Think differently. Sharp-minded. Motivate self. Dont appreciate praises. Highspirited. Well-built, tough. Deep love, emotions. Romantic. Uncertain in relationships. Homely. Hardworking. High abilities. Trustworthy. Honest. Keepsecrets. Cant control emotions. Unpredictable.

Nicked from
and all over my flist



Hmm, I knew I was weird, but this..

B+
You're a pro at going with the flow You love to kick back and take in everything life has to offer A total joy to be around, people crave your stability. While you're totally laid back, you can have bouts of hyperactivity. Get into a project you love, and you won't stop until it's done You're passionate - just selective about your passions

To anyone who may read this:

A late

 

Happy Easter!

I really thought I would be around more than I have recently, but apparently not, so I'm not going to say I'm back this time. I just hope I'll have more time to be around.

And , sweetie, I'm working on the changes you suggested, thank you very much!

Love to you!

Late as always but because the sweet   asked me to:

 


1. Total amount of music files on your computer?
Just a few, I don't save music on my PC.
2. The last CD you bought was:
best of Marilyn Manson
3. What was the last song you listened to before reading this message?
Kent 500+
4. Write down five songs you often listen to or that mean a lot to you.
 1. Kent Sundance Kid - because it sort of tells the story of a lost frienship in a way very similar to something I've experienced in RL (and it always makes me cry)
 2.The Police Every breath you take - because it describes obsession in a very fascinating way
 3.Weeping Willows Touch me- for this phrase: I'm just as human as a human can be...
 4.Depeche Mode The policy of truth -Hmm, I'm not going to analyze the reasons why
 5. Frankie goes to Hollywood- The power of love- because it really describes it

Not a very happy collection I guess, but I guess I'm a sucker for angst when it comes to music too...

Thank you , , for your lovely postcard. It arrived today and really brightened my day.

And the children, especially my daughter, loved the surprise!

((Love and hugs))

I'm not good at this, I just  wanted to wish you a happy birthday.

I'm so happy to have met you, you're both a wonderful person and a good beta.

Have a nice day, sweetie!

So I'm back home. I really like the US, (except for the fact that Bush was re-elected), but Sweden is home to me.Well, have been for a week actually, but I haven't had neither the time or the energy to update my LJ until now. I'm at work at the moment, working during nighttime again to get some tests done. ( I should be home sleeping, but since I'm a more or less chronic insomniac I do like this a little too often.)

At this way , I  will be at home with my children during daytime and that means a lot.

Just wanted to thank everybody who sent me encouraging comments, it really means a lot to me. I still have some things to deal with, but I will try to read some stories and write some.

This will be a short entry, I don't have time for anything else. I'm going away for a couple of weeks, will be back in the beginning of November.

I'm off to Florida, but I wish the circumstances were better the first time I'm going there. May be cryptic, but i'm not in the mood to talk at the moment.

I will postpart 2 of memories of red wine when I get back. "Hidden Scars" is with my beta right at the moment.

Take care everybody that may read this.

Goodbye.

Am still at work despite the fact that it is in the middle of the night. Should definitely concentrate on that like I 've been doing the last four days, not wasting time on LJ.

I have never posted images before, but I will give it a try. This is a manip I made as a teaser for an AU-fic that I could not stop myself from start to write ( not Memories of Red Wine). I think I will call this "Lashmarks". It's going to be angsty, as can be seen in the picture under the cut.

Off for mountain climbing for three weeks in the north of Sweden (Jokkmokk).
My story will be updated when I get back.

Take the quiz: "Who is your famous soul mate? (For Girls)"

Orlando Bloom
Gwrrr...you've gotten Orlando Bloom! A romantic English man that loves to recite poems..how lucky can you get? (Just so you know, Orlando's mine!!) I was lucky, I guess...and I managed to copy it as well...
